message.content:
There are several verb tenses in English, including:

1. Present simple (e.g., "I go to school")
2. Present continuous (e.g., "I am going to school")
3. Present perfect (e.g., "I have gone to school")
4. Present perfect continuous (e.g., "I have been going to school")
5. Past simple (e.g., "I went to school")
6. Past continuous (e.g., "I was going to school")
7. Past perfect (e.g., "I had gone to school")
8. Past perfect continuous (e.g., "I had been going to school")
9. Future simple (e.g., "I will go to school")
10. Future continuous (e.g., "I will be going to school")
11. Future perfect (e.g., "I will have gone to school")
12. Future perfect continuous (e.g., "I will have been going to school")

It's worth noting that there are also other verb tenses, such as the conditional and the subjunctive mood, but these are less commonly used in everyday conversation.
